Citations
Date:  0/10/1890
Source:  NZ Farmer
Author:
Vol / Page:  410
Edition:
Quote:  Where potatoes are frost-bitten it would be easy enough to mow off the tops and earth them over, which would have the same effect as the Maori treatment, and save the crop.
